[The latest numbers from WHO are unchanged on Sun 1 Nov 2015 from those it reported as of 25 Oct 2015 -- see ProMED Ebola update 121 (click on the archive number on the See Also list below). I edited out the probable and suspected cases, which include a high proportion of Lassa fever, severe malaria, and acute cases of other diseases, inflating the overall totals. Also see ref. "Undercounting of Ebola cases" in [4] Research below. - Mod.JW]

