[2] CDC update 28 Oct 2015
Date: 28 Oct 2015 16:43:10 GMT
Source: Bioprepwatch [edited]
http://bioprepwatch.com/stories/510645718-cdc-issues-ebola-outbreak-update


CDC issues Ebola outbreak update
----------------
The U.S. Centers for Disease Prevention and Control (CDC) released updated information regarding the outbreak of the Ebola virus in West Africa on Wed [28 Oct 2015].

In this update, they reported a total of 28 575 cases associated with the outbreak. This includes 15 243 cases that have been confirmed by a laboratory along with suspected and probable cases. [Note that in the early stages, lab capacity was inadequate and very many cases were never lab tested. - Mod.JW] Since the outbreak began, 11 313 people [are reported to] have succumbed to the disease. It has also been reported that, if Sierra Leone does not see additional cases through 7 Nov 2015, it will be declared free of Ebola transmission. According to the report, all contacts associated with prior cases have completed the 21-day monitoring period. The last patient to have had the disease was cleared on 25 Sep 2015.

The World Health Organization (WHO) reported 3 confirmed cases of the disease in Guinea leading up to 25 Oct 2015. Liberia, Sierra Leone and Guinea have been the countries to see the heaviest impact of this outbreak. Over the course of the epidemic, 36 cases were reported in countries outside of the outbreak's main zone.

The USA lifted specialized entry screening for travelers coming from Liberia, but these remain in effect for those traveling from Sierra Leone and Guinea. Liberia was declared free of transmission as of 3 Sep 2015.

