[3] Guinea: 3 new cases of Ebola
Date: 29 Oct 2015
Source: News24 [edited]
http://www.news24.com/Africa/News/Guinea-records-3-new-cases-of-Ebola-brings-total-to-9-20151029


Guinea records 3 new cases of Ebola, brings total to 9
---------------
[According to Fode Tass Sylla, a spokesperson for the national center for the fight against Ebola virus disease (EVD), who spoke on Wed (28 Oct 2015), 3 more people in Guinea have contracted EVD. The 3 new EVD patients were infected in Forecariah (western Guinea) from the family of a woman who died of EVD and whose body was handled without appropriate protection. According to Sylla, "In all, 9 sick people are being treated at our centers throughout the country and most are connected to the dead woman," he told Reuters. He also said authorities had known of the 3 new cases since Sat (24 Oct 2015)." Most -- but not all. - Mod.JW]

1 Nov 2015 Guinea: Newborn tests positive for Ebola despite healthy parents
http://en.starafrica.com/news/guinea-newborn-tests-positive-for-ebola-despite-healthy-parents.html
[A baby born to "healthy parents" has tested positive for the Ebola virus in the town of Forecariah in Guinea near the border with Sierra Leone, Fode Tass Sylla, the communication officer of the national response coordination against the epidemic confirmed on Sun [1 Nov 2015]. I wonder why the parents were tested in the 1st place - were they contacts? - Mod.JW]

28 Oct 2015 Sierra Leone: EID: Ebola Virus Disease complicated by late-onset encephalitis and polyarthritis
https://flutrackers.com/forum/forum/welcome-to-the-scientific-library/ebola-research-studies-papers-academia/740432-eid-ebola-virus-disease-complicated-by-late-onset-encephalitis-and-polyarthritis-sierra-leone
[Ebola virus disease (EVD) is usually an acute illness, but increasing evidence exists of persistent infections and post-EVD syndromes. A case of EBOV encephalitis is reported in this journal letter]
Ref: Howlett P, Brown C, Helderman T, Brooks T, Lisk D, Deen G, et al. Ebola virus disease complicated by late-onset encephalitis and polyarthritis, Sierra Leone [letter]. Emerg Infect Dis. 2016 Jan [date cited]. http://dx.doi.org/10.3201/eid2201.151212 DOI: 10.3201/eid2201.151212

